September 2025)\nA significant rebuild of Codex CLI was announced:\n\n**New Features:**\n- **Image attachment support** - Directly attach and share screenshots, wireframes, and design diagrams in CLI\n- **Todo list tracking** - Codex generates task lists to track progress on complex work\n- **External tool integration** - Web search and MCP protocol integration for connecting external systems\n- **Improved tool usage accuracy**\n\n**UI Improvements:**\n- Better tool call and diff display formatting\n- Three approval modes:\n  - Read-only (requires explicit approval)\n  - Automatic (full workspace access, but requires approval for operations outside workspace)\n  - Full access (can read arbitrary files and run commands with network access)\n- Support for compressing conversation state for managing long sessions\n\n### Earlier Updates\n- **v0.23.0** (August 2025): Added dynamic model switching capability in CLI, including support for \"gpt-5 high\"\n- **GPT-5 as default model** (August 2025): GPT-5 became the default model for Codex CLI, accessible through ChatGPT subscription plans (Plus, Pro, Team)\n\n**Installation:** Users can update via: `npm install -g @openai/codex`\n\n**Note:** The search results don't show a specific dedicated February 2026 changelog, but rather announcements about the broader Codex ecosystem upgrades that include CLI improvements.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
