      "Based on my web search, I couldn't find specific Reddit discussions about \"Cursor Slack Background Agents\" with reactions from **February 2026**, since that date is still in the future. However, I found extensive information about Cursor's Background Agents and Slack integration features that were released in **2025**, along with various user reactions. Here's what I found:\n\n## Cursor Background Agents & Slack Integration Overview\n\n### Key Features Released (2025):\n1. **Background Agent Infrastructure**: AI agents that can work autonomously in the background without real-time human supervision\n2. **Slack Integration**: Users can trigger agents by typing `@Cursor` in Slack channels\n3. **Web & Mobile Support**: Browser-based and mobile phone access to manage agents\n\n### User Reactions Found:\n\n**Positive Reactions:**\n- \"用了 Cursor 的后台 Agent 一周了，真香。不用重复输提示，它自己创建 PR，还能在云端工作区跑。这就是编程的未来。\" (Used Cursor's background agent for a week, it's amazing. This is the future of programming.)\n- \"以后可以摸鱼刷代码，而不是刷短视频了。\" (Now you can procrastinate by browsing code instead of short videos.)\n- \"这绝对是 AI Agent 的发展方向！后台、并行处理复杂任务，就是知识工作的下一站。太牛了。\" (This is definitely the direction of AI Agent development! Background, parallel processing of complex tasks is the next stop for knowledge work.)\n\n**Skeptical/Critical Reactions:**\n- \"等 AI 编码超级靠谱的时候，这功能会很酷。但现在还不行，我推任何代码前都得做一大堆测试。\" (When AI coding becomes super reliable, this feature will be cool. But not now, I still need to do a lot of testing before pushing code.)\n- \"我没法想象让 AI 在那自己跑，回头一看，发现它拉了一堆 [garbage]。\" (I can't imagine letting AI run on its own, then looking back and finding it created a mess.)\n- Cost concerns: \"这过程得烧掉多少 token 啊……我见过有人不到一周就烧了三四千刀。\" (How many tokens will this burn... I've seen someone burn $3-4k in less than a week.)\n\n### Context:\n- Cursor's CEO stated: \"By 2026, AI Agents will handle at least 20% of developers' daily work\"\n- The technology represents a shift from \"real-time copilot\" to \"autonomous background employee\"\n- Currently requires Max mode (premium tier)\n- Agents can work in cloud workspaces and create pull requests automatically\n\n**Note**: The search results are from mid-2025 (June-July 2025), so February 2026 discussions would not exist yet. You may need to check back closer to or after that date to find actual Reddit discussions from February 2026."
